-align="center">3 sets</td><td>15 reps</td><td>45 seconds</td></tr><tr><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">Dumbbell Seated Extension</td><td class="has-text-align-center" data-align="center">3 sets</td><td>15 reps</td><td>45 seconds</td></tr></tbody></table><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">3-Day Dumbbell Workout Split Day 2</figcaption></figure>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Day-3">Day 3</h3>



<p>Day 3 shifts focus to dynamic strength, emphasizing balance, coordination, and fine-tuning muscle definition. This workout is designed to target the legs, glutes, arms, shoulders, and back while improving stability and control.</p>



<p>It begins with movements designed to build functional strength. Maximum voluntary isometric contraction, or MVIC, is a measure of how much a muscle activates during an exercise. For example, step-ups achieve gluteus maximus activation levels as <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7039033/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">high as 125% MVIC</a>. This makes them a cornerstone exercise for anyone aiming to build lower-body strength and stability.</p>



<p>As the workout progresses, the focus shifts to developing arm, back, and shoulder definition. The carefully selected combination of pushing, pulling, and curling exercises creates a comprehensive <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/upper-body-dumbbell-workout" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">upper body dumbbell workout</a>. Every movement is designed to improve symmetry and functional performance while refining the finer details of your physique.</p>



